subvertex.name: ask user to think of an animal

ownedComment.body: Think of an animal and keep it in mind, I will ask you several questions and will try to guess the animal you have in mind, select 'got one' to proceed.
Answer this question by selecting either 'yes' or 'no'.
I cannot guess the animal you have in mind, you may reveal it here, select 'this is the animal' to proceed. The value must not be empty.

I will remember the animal you had in mind, but I would also need a differentiator question. This question should make the difference between the animal in the most recent attempt to guess, and the one you had in mind. The value must not be empty.
I have successfully guessed your animal, please select 'continue' to proceed.
Click to confirm you have an animal in mind.
Enter a differentiator question indicating the difference between the last animal and the one you had in mind.
This question expresses the difference between the last guessed animal and the one the user actually had in mind.
You may reveal the animal you had in mind here.
Click here if the answer is correct.
Click here if the answer is wrong.
Indicates if item is the root of the decision tree. Only one item can have "true" for this attribute.
Abstract. Realized by Animal and Question.
Returns the root of the decision tree.
The default "decision" exception thrown, during decision processing.
